<subSubSection id="ECB3BB44E62BEA6BB9BD160A8464788B" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" type="description">
<paragraph id="FFA033CD10073549B399F1130DACCF0A" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Diagnostic description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EDA99DCE446BCBD7FA74D5ADC54C26FB" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
Overall brown. Pronotal disc (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9E037A91ADCFCED4AB1880EFA9225535" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Costalampys minima sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Male terminal segments, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-B); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (C; E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (D; F-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543221" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">18D</figureCitation>
) brown, with light brown vittae, expansions testaceous, mildly translucent anteriorly. Elytron (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F45913E6A54D4B1685FB3C4161913808" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Costalampys minima sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Male terminal segments, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-B); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (C; E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (D; F-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543221" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">18A</figureCitation>
) light brown, without any pale-yellow longitudinal stripe. Legs (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E6A0CB7112900A5B5697C77A4355553C" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Costalampys minima sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Male terminal segments, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-B); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (C; E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (D; F-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543221" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">18B</figureCitation>
) brown, except for trochanters, which are light brown. Sternum VIII (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0C3AFF76C83D01C2CCAA27AA3E91FDE2" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Costalampys minima sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Male terminal segments, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-B); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (C; E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (D; F-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543221" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">18F</figureCitation>
) entirely translucent. Pygidium entirely dark brown or with paired translucent, elongate spots a 1/3
<normalizedToken id="F6803A124CF6026E26C50FC8DED8A8C6" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as wide as pygidium.
</paragraph>
<caption id="E68D2ED3A52D38F4CBE5B5CC83C4F350" doi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543221" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" start="Figure 18" startId="F18">
<paragraph id="E833D0CE69756406234A85CA3EC8F6BF" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
<emphasis id="42EF8F629C805EBA3592D3C6C78628BF" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Figure 18.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="0E3D20DAD27804E5764BF97C358B1FEF" authority="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" authorityName="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Costalampys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Costalampys minima" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minima">
<emphasis id="D524A24E194404FDB359A23299C0DD4C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Costalampys minima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="99EC3872F8081831B816A96ADA3FD349" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">sp. nov. A</emphasis>
, Male habitus, dorsal view; 
<emphasis id="EE022F452BA8EE8B6BD629AB73378872" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">B</emphasis>
, Male habitus, ventral view; 
<emphasis id="4B9B884539EA67A88A97CCCCF6FD8668" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">C</emphasis>
, Male antenna, lateral view; 
<emphasis id="63CC1345297CD523C2DAB62577884F5B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">D</emphasis>
, Male pronotum, dorsal view; 
<emphasis id="E6176FF25919C91B25EEA1F70F239B6B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">E</emphasis>
, Male terminal segments, ventral view; 
<emphasis id="83BB79410930DDB40E81AD933EE170AF" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">F</emphasis>
, Pygidium, dorsal view; 
<emphasis id="2DAE428FC8CE403F7432171950D8BBCD" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">G</emphasis>
, Syntergite, dorsal view; 
<emphasis id="1E8ACB90EDCE3BC1CF98118E153B7584" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">H</emphasis>
, Sternum IX, Ventral view; 
<emphasis id="67E8596870A509B2FC49E73645E2E08F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">I</emphasis>
, Aedeagus, dorsal view; 
<emphasis id="68F714797C60632AD8DA297E17D092D3" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">J</emphasis>
, Aedeagus, lateral view; 
<emphasis id="CA4423DEC3A4A7E0BEE29ADE06CACBBD" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">K</emphasis>
, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-B); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (C; E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (D; F-K).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="58FB008E33BAF3A74F7AD47AB31D1136" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
Pronotum (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="62262394EF0A26547ACA6679BE042BA7" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Costalampys minima sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Male terminal segments, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-B); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (C; E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (D; F-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543221" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">18D</figureCitation>
) with sides rounded, divergent posteriorly. 
<emphasis id="FCA283EE9088B5331B8D5742ED7260DC" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Male.</emphasis>
Total length = 5.4-6.3 mm (aver. 5.85 mm); Pronotal length = 1.0-1.3 mm (aver. 1.15 mm); Pronotal width = 1.7-2.0 mm (aver. 1.85 mm); Elytral length = 4.7-5.0 mm (aver. 4.85 mm); Elytral width = 1.2-1.4 mm (aver. 1.3 mm). Antennomere III with lamella about 2.x longer than core antennomere. Sternum VI and VII (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="06DD91F299E5187DF9AD732A84193CCF" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Costalampys minima sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Male terminal segments, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-B); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (C; E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (D; F-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543221" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">18B, E</figureCitation>
) with translucent spots about 1/2
<normalizedToken id="36C49EAB9DE535E91CE2BC79163A336D" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long and 1/6
<normalizedToken id="B34C839E8373397984D1A345CE1792B6" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as wide as sterna, lanterns rudimentary. Sterna VI and VII (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7B897F4B96A8CA6E8958D342A6FA4EAB" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Costalampys minima sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Male terminal segments, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-B); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (C; E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (D; F-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543221" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">18B, E</figureCitation>
) with minute, central translucent round spots that look like rudimentary lanterns. Sternum VIII with posterior margin bisinuose. Pygidium with sides rounded, posterior corners weakly developed, posterior margin rounded to almost straight. Syntergite (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="26D9ABF9EE6518EF46335F3EDDD8FF85" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Costalampys minima sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Male terminal segments, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-B); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (C; E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (D; F-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543221" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">18G, H</figureCitation>
) boomerang-shaped (with anterior margin strongly curved). Phallus (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B40201CF98BF7DF51C85D3B738500FA1" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Costalampys minima sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Male antenna, lateral view; D, Male pronotum, dorsal view; E, Male terminal segments, ventral view; F, Pygidium, dorsal view; G, Syntergite, dorsal view; H, Sternum IX, Ventral view; I, Aedeagus, dorsal view; J, Aedeagus, lateral view; K, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-B); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (C; E); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (D; F-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543221" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">18I-K</figureCitation>
) with dorsal plate curved almost straight in lateral view, with sides straight and acuminate at apical half. Paramere apex curved ventrally, ventral projection (lateral view) rudimentary. 
<emphasis id="80FCE173E5F6CE0CEC89033865875641" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Female.</emphasis>
unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A4D804CF57184FA6D6389DDC1893175B" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="1B1264701124B92BA645C86B6820A1A5" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="14BCBE54CEC026E36F0D313473FEEEDD" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
<taxonomicName id="284FE77851F1CEC045F324DEDC0A8086" authority="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" authorityName="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Costalampys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Costalampys minima" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minima">
